# EasyTrading

Multi-DEX trading client for .NET (HyperLiquid live; Aster + dYdX v4 planned). See `AGENTS.md` for full guidance.

## Status

HyperLiquid is `1.0.0` — production-grade:
- Read endpoints, write endpoints (EIP-712 signed), and WebSocket streams all work end-to-end against live mainnet
- Pre-flight order validation rejects bad tick / lot / min-notional client-side before sending
- REST retry policy: 3 attempts, exponential backoff, `Retry-After` honoured
- WS gap recovery for user streams (MyFills/MyOrders/MyFundings): REST catch-up on reconnect, deduped
- Builder-fee routing is automatic (auto-attach + auto-approve on first order)
- Integration-test verified

## Core rules

- `decimal` for all money values; never `double` / `float`
- `Async` suffix on every async method; `CancellationToken ct = default` last parameter
- Methods grouped by entity: `Orders`, `Positions`, `Markets`, `Trades`, `Account`, `Transfers`, `Streams`, plus HL-only `Vaults` / `Staking`
- WebSocket streams use `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` with `await foreach`
- Check `client.Capabilities.HasFlag(ExchangeCapabilities.X)` before calling optional features
- Typed exceptions: `RateLimitException`, `InsufficientFundsException`, `InvalidOrderException`, `AuthenticationException`, `SigningException`
- `from` / `to` for time-range parameters

## HyperLiquid specifics

- Prefer agent wallets over the master private key — call `IAccount.ApproveAgentAsync(...)` once, then trade with the agent's key
- Network: `HyperLiquidNetwork.Mainnet` or `.Testnet`
- Builder fee is automatic; users opt out by setting `options.BuilderFee` to a zero rate or routing to their own address

## DI registration

```csharp
services.AddEasyTrading()
        .AddHyperLiquid(o =>
        {
            o.Network     = HyperLiquidNetwork.Mainnet;
            o.Credentials = new HyperLiquidCredentials("0xMaster", privKey, agentName: "my-bot");
        });
```

Inject `IHyperLiquidExchange` (HL-specific surface — adds Vaults/Staking) or `IExchangeClient` (cross-DEX).

## Common operations

```csharp
// Market data
var mids = await ex.Markets.GetAllMidsAsync(ct);
var book = await ex.Markets.GetOrderBookAsync("BTC", depth: 10, ct);

// Trading
await ex.Orders.PlaceLimitAsync("BTC", OrderSide.Buy, price: 60_000m, size: 0.01m, tif: TimeInForce.Alo, ct: ct);
await ex.Orders.CancelAllAsync(ct: ct);
await ex.Positions.SetLeverageAsync("BTC", 10, MarginMode.Cross, ct);
await ex.Positions.CloseAsync("BTC", ct);

// Transfers / approvals (user-signed under the hood)
await ex.Transfers.WithdrawAsync("0xExternal", 100m, ct);
await ex.Transfers.SpotToPerpAsync(50m, ct);
await ex.Account.ApproveAgentAsync("0xAgentAddr", "easy-bot", ct);

// WebSocket streams
await foreach (var trade in ex.Streams.TradesAsync("BTC", ct))
    Console.WriteLine($"{trade.Trade.Price} {trade.Trade.Size}");

await foreach (var fill in ex.Streams.MyFillsAsync(ct))
    Console.WriteLine($"{fill.Fill.Symbol} {fill.Fill.Price}");
```

## Anti-patterns

- Don't `new HyperLiquidClient(...)` when DI is available — use `AddHyperLiquid()`
- Don't use `double` / `float` for money
- Don't forget `CancellationToken` in long-running or `await foreach` loops
- Don't catch raw `Exception` — catch typed exceptions
- Don't hold the master private key in production — use an agent wallet
- Don't call HL-only features (`Vaults`, `Staking`) on `IExchangeClient` — use `IHyperLiquidExchange`
